Hain Celestial Group, Inc.

1111 Marcus Avenue North New Hyde Park
New York NY 11042 United States
Phone: +1 516-___-____
Fax: +1 516-___-____
http://www.hain.com





68
Managers




50
IT employees




$95.7MEST.
IT Budget




Hain Celestial Group, Inc. is a natural and organic food and personal care products company that operates in North America and Europe. It includes the following brands: Celestial Seasonings, Terra, Garden of Eatin', Health Valley, WestSoy, Earth's Best, Arrowhead Mills,… MoreHain Celestial Group, Inc. is a natural and organic food and personal care products company that operates in North America and Europe. It includes the following brands: Celestial Seasonings, Terra, Garden of Eatin', Health Valley, WestSoy, Earth's Best, Arrowhead Mills, DeBoles, Hain Pure Foods, FreeBird, Hollywood, Spectrum Naturals, Spectrum Essentials, Walnut Acres Organic, Imagine Foods, Rice Dream, Soy Dream, Rosetto, Ethnic Gourmet, Yves Veggie Cuisine, Linda McCartney, Realeat, Lima, Grains Noirs, Natumi, JASON, Zia, Natural Skincare, Avalon Organics, Alba Botanica, and Queen Helene.
• Hain Celestial acquired Empire Kosher and its Empire Kosher Poultry subsidiary, in March, 2015.  Empire operates as a separate brand division.

Even though Hain Celestial Group's corporate headquarters is located in Melville, NY, the IT department operates primarily from the data… More• Hain Celestial acquired Empire Kosher and its Empire Kosher Poultry subsidiary, in March, 2015.  Empire operates as a separate brand division.

Even though Hain Celestial Group's corporate headquarters is located in Melville, NY, the IT department operates primarily from the data center and central call center in Boulder, CO. Selected IT staff members work in Melville.

Hain Celestial Group, Inc. has previously developed new IT security initiatives for the network throughout the company. 

Hain Celestial Canada's IT group is mostly autonomous, but since the Canada division is smaller so is their IT department. Some applications used in Canada are hosted by the US group. BYOD is not something the Canada group is considering. 

Virtualization and cloud computing were areas of focus in the past. The company has virtualized its servers and planned virtualize its desktops in the past. 

Executives at the corporate headquarters are in charge of infrastructure, financial applications/systems, and telephony and telecommunications. The location in Boulder, CO, features directors and managers that oversee IT client services (help desk functions), electronic data interchange (EDI), and supply chain systems. 

Hain Celestial Group often buys different food product brands. As a result, the company's storage capacity needs tend to increase over time. The department is dealing with this issue through virtualization.

Hain Celestial Group, Inc. has led storage initiatives in the areas of data protection and recovery software, storage replication software.  

Hain Celestial Group, Inc. describes managing white space, growth and change as its biggest storage headache. Its top storage pain points are the need for better and more reliable off-site disaster recovery, WAN being too slow, and data loss. 

Hain Celestial Group, Inc. uses disk backup across DAS environment to back up its hybrid of block and file data. It uses EVault as its main backup application. Its daily and weekly total data backup is 2TB and 45TB respectively, with a 5-6 hour backup window. Its backup growth is around 10. Relating to its remote locations, data is backed up locally.  

The IT budget is typically finalized in Q1.





