Home / Investing / Hain Celestial Group (NDAQ:HAIN) target upped to $50.00, issued a ratings update earlier today by Maxim Group

Hain Celestial Group (NDAQ:HAIN) target upped to $50.00, issued a ratings update earlier today by Maxim Group


By Al Wild


Updated: July 26, 2017




Displaying a price of $39.48, Hain Celestial Group (NDAQ:HAIN) traded 0.34% higher on the day. With the last stock price up 18.05% from the 200-day moving average, compared to the S&P 500 which has increased 0.06% over the date range.  Hain Celestial Group has recorded a 50-day average of $37.49 and a two hundred day average of $37.23.  Trading volume was down over the average, with 1,443,821 shares of HAIN changing hands under the typical 2,378,160 
Hain Celestial Group (NDAQ:HAIN) had its stock price target increased to $50.00 by Maxim Group in an issued report announced 07/13/2017.  The bumped up target suggests a possible upside of 0.27% based on  the company's most recent close.
Performance Chart

Hain Celestial Group has a 52 week low of $31.01 and a 52 week high of $56.99   The company’s market cap is presently $0.
A total of 19 brokerages have released a research note on Hain Celestial Group.  Ten brokers rating the stock a strong buy, 6 brokers rating the stock a buy, six brokerages rating the company a hold, one brokerage rating the stock a underperform, and finally 0 firms rating the stock a sell with a consensus target of $50.47.
More About Hain Celestial Group (NDAQ:HAIN)
The Hain Celestial Group, Inc. is an organic and natural products company. The Company and its subsidiaries manufacture, market, distribute and sell organic and natural products under brand names which are sold as better-for-you products. The Company's segments include United States, United Kingdom, Hain Pure Protein and Rest of World. Its Rest of World segment includes Canada and Europe. The Company's brand names include Almond Dream, Arrowhead Mills, Bearitos, BluePrint, Celestial Seasonings, Cully & Sully, Danival, DeBoles, Earth's Best, Ella's Kitchen, Empire, Europe's Best, Farmhouse Fare, Frank Cooper's, FreeBird, Gale's, Garden of Eatin', GG UniqueFiber, Hain Pure Foods, Hartley's, Health Valley, Imagine, Johnson's Juice Co., Joya, Kosher Valley, Lima, The Greek Gods, Tilda, Walnut Acres, WestSoy, Yves Veggie Cuisine and Yorkshire Provender. Its personal care products are marketed under the Alba Botanica, Avalon Organics, Earth's Best, JASON, Live Clean and Queen Helene brands.

