The Hain Celestial Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:HAIN) Stock Closed Significantly Above Its 50 Day Average 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsThe Hain Celestial Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:HAIN) Stock Closed Significantly Above Its 50 Day Average
July 25, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Shares are trading at $43.79 which is marginally higher than the 50 day moving average which is $37.03 and which is marginally over the 200 day moving average of $37.15.  The 50 day moving average went up by +18.26% and the 200 day average moved up $6.64.  The Hain Celestial Group, Inc. shares had a trading volume of 80K on Tuesday.  Shares saw a steep decrease in trading volume of 94.39% under the normal average daily volume. 
 Here are a few other firms who have also updated their positions.   As of the end of the quarter Investment House LLC had disposed of  a total of 17,800 shares trimming its position 42.5%. The value of the investment in (HAIN) decreased from $1,559,000 to $936,000 decreasing 40.0% for the reporting period. As of quarter end Rothschild Investment Corp /il had sold 3,925 shares trimming its stake by 32.6%. The value of the total investment in The Hain Celestial Group, Inc. went from $448,000 to $315,000 a change of $133,000 since the last quarter.
 Cedar Wealth Management, LLC trimmed its holdings by selling 15 shares a decrease of 0.5% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Cedar Wealth Management, LLC owns 3,005 shares valued at $117,000. The value of the position overall is up by 4.5%. Dubuque Bank & Trust Co augmented its position by buying 693 shares an increase of 10.7% as of 06/30/2017. Dubuque Bank & Trust Co currently owns 7,188 shares worth $279,000. The total value of its holdings increased 15.3%.
  On July 13 the company was upgraded from “Perform” to “Buy” by analysts at Maxim Group. On June 23 the company was rated “Neutral” in a report from JP Morgan which was a cut from the previous “Overweight” rating.        Advertisement






 On November 18 the stock rating was upgraded to “Neutral” from “Neutral” in a statement from Atlantic Equities. On November 18, 2016 the stock rating was changed to a “Neutral” according to a Bank of America report which is up from the previous “” rating.
 Equity analyst Susquehanna added HAIN to its research portfolio setting a rating of “Positive”. On September 15 UBS held the company rating at “Sell” but lowered the price target from $49.00 to $33.00.
 In the market the company is trading up by 0.07% since yesterday’s close of $43.76.  As of the latest earnings report the EPS was $-0.21 and is projected to be $1.20 for the current year with 103,697,000 shares currently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $0.23 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $1.66. 
 The Hain Celestial Group, Inc., launched on May 19, 1993, is an organic and natural products company. The Company and its subsidiaries manufacture, market, distribute and sell organic and natural products under brand names which are sold as better-for-you products. The Business’s segments include United States, United Kingdom, Hain Pure Protein and Rest of World. Its Rest of World segment includes Canada and Europe. The Business’s subsidiaries include Hain Pure Protein Corporation, which processes, markets and distributes antibiotic-free, organic and other poultry products, and EK Holdings, Inc., which grows, processes and sells kosher poultry and other products under the Empire and Kosher Valley brand names..
